snippet: Only 21 percent of registered voters turned out for the Los Angeles mayoral election last week, and some residents are both embarrassed and concerned.
abstract: Only 21 percent of registered voters turned out for Los Angeles mayoral election, lowest rate for primary without an incumbent since at least 1978, and some residents are both embarrassed and concerned.
lead_paragraph: Only 21 percent of registered voters turned out for the Los Angeles mayoral election last week, and some residents are both embarrassed and concerned.

headline.seo: Los Angeles Frets About Its Low Voter Turnout
headline.main: Los Angeles Frets After Low Turnout to Elect Mayor
